const e="Built-in Appliances FAQ",t="Find answers to common questions about LG built-in appliances, from installation tips to troubleshooting and maintenance advice.",i="Frequently Asked Questions",n=[{id:1,q:"I want to remove the gas oven and install a built-in gas cooktop and storage cabinet. Is that possible?",a:"It’s possible. Simply attach the lower cabinet and top plate to the space where the gas oven was removed and install a built-in gas cooktop on the top plate. (Construction methods may vary depending on site conditions, so please contact a LG Kitchen Specialty partner in advance.)"},{id:2,q:"Can't I just use the built-in dishwasher without combining to furniture?",a:`There is no problem at all in using the product. However, since built-in products are manufactured to be combined with furniture, if the furniture is not combined, the body itself does not come out as a finished product, making it visually unsightly. 
Please keep this in mind.`},{id:3,q:"Is it impossible to replace it once installed?",a:"Replacement is possible after installation. You can reinstall the product as long as the built-in installation space is secured."},{id:4,q:"Can I remove a built-in appliance attached to kitchen furniture, without damaging it?",a:"Built-in products can of course be removed and reinstalled. There is a risk of scratches on kitchen furniture or products, so please contact a professional built-in installation engineer for reinstallation. also call an LG expert to advise how to do it."},{id:5,q:"What if you want to change your kitchen with LG built-in products?",a:"If it is a built-in product (gas oven, cooking hob), it must be installed according to the kitchen furniture, so you should contact a kitchen furniture company or interior design company to check the type and size of the kitchen furniture. After consultation, if the installation space for the built-in product is secured, you can request the kitchen furniture company to install the LG built-in product. (Currently, LG built-in products are being consulted and sold at LG Premium Brand shop also multi brand dealer stores, and kitchen interior specialty.)"},{id:6,q:"What if you want to replace just the product after decorating your kitchen with built-in products?",a:"The existing built-in product can be dismantled and replaced with another built-in product. But need to check dimensions of existing built-in product to fit new one."},{id:7,q:"What are the installation requirements for LG Built-in Appliances?",a:"LG Built-in Appliances require professional installation to ensure proper fit and functionality. It's recommended to check the appliance dimensions and electrical requirements beforehand. We provide installation guidelines and recommend hiring a certified installer for the best results."},{id:8,q:"Can LG Built-in Appliances be installed in any kitchen layout?",a:"Yes, LG Built-in Appliances are designed to fit seamlessly into a variety of kitchen layouts. However, we recommend consulting with a kitchen designer to ensure the appliances are compatible with your specific layout and to maximize space efficiency."},{id:9,q:"How do LG Built-in Appliances compare in quality to other brands?",a:"LG Built-in Appliances are known for their superior quality, reliability, and advanced technology. We use high-quality materials and rigorous testing standards to ensure durability and long-lasting performance, making them a top choice among premium appliance brands."},{id:10,q:"What advanced features do LG Built-in Appliances offer?",a:"LG Built-in Appliances come equipped with state-of-the-art features such as SmartThinQ™ technology for remote control and monitoring, InstaView® for quick access, and TrueSteam™ for enhanced cleaning. These features are designed to enhance convenience, efficiency, and user experience."}],a={title:e,subtitle:t,sectionTitle:i,questions:n};export{a as default,n as questions,i as sectionTitle,t as subtitle,e as title};
